'''Commander Lydia Fullore''' is the leader of the Kourend [[Royal Guard]]. As leader of the Royal Guard, she ensures that they are well trained and supplied.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commander Fullore|quote=The Kourend Royal Guard protect and serve the ruler of Kourend. As their leader, I am responsible for ensuring that the Royal Guard are well trained and well supplied.}} She is found on the {{FloorNumber|uk=0}} of [[Kourend Castle]].

==History==
===Service in the Shayzien Army===
Unlike other people in [[Hosidius]], Lydia wished to join the [[Shayzien Army]]; as a child, she took note of a Shayzien patrol that went around her house, and she would come out to wave at them as she went by.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commander Fullore|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=Back when I was a girl, there was this Shayzien patrol that would go past our house each morning. Every day I would run out to wave at them as they went by.}} Despite her parents' desire for her to become a farmer or chef, jobs commonly taken by those who live in Hosidius, she would eventually enlist in the Shayzien Army.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commander Fullore|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=For as long as I can remember, I always wanted to join the army. 'Become a farmer or a chef,' my parents would say to me. 'The army isn't for you.' But I knew what I wanted, and I knew nothing would stop me from getting it.}}

During her time as a soldier, she was part of a squad requested by the [[Kourend Council]] to deal with a gang of thieves who had children in their ranks.{{CiteNPC|npc=Martin Holt|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=I remember a gang of thieves a few years back that used them heavily. The kids could get places the adults couldn't. No one ever suspected them either. They were such a problem that the Council had to get Lord Shayzien to send some soldiers in to deal with them. Lydia was one of them.}} Though the operation was successful, she was distraught at the fact that the Council threw not just the men, but the children in prison, too.{{CiteNPC|npc=Martin Holt|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=The Council had them all thrown in prison, even the children. Lydia was distraught.}}

===Leader of the Royal Guard===
Eventually, Lydia would work directly for the Kourend Council as leader of the [[Royal Guard]]. During this time, she would meet [[Martin Holt]], who was employed by the Council, and began a relationship with him.{{CiteNPC|npc=Martin Holt|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=I'm sure Lydia didn't tell you everything about herself either. We were together once, you know.}} However, their relationship fell apart after some time as Martin began to see the Council's flaws and she eventually moved on to a relationship with [[Captain Ginea]], which also fell apart eventually.{{CiteNPC|npc=Martin Holt|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=...she was ever loyal to the Council. In the end she decided I wasn't her type, and went off with that Captain Ginea instead. Of course, that didn't work out either.}}
[[File:A Kingdom Divided - Andrews thanks.png|left|thumb|Andrews keeping a watch on Lydia after the incident with Hughes.]]
After the arrest of Councillor [[Sophia Hughes]] and her subsequent escape,{{CiteNPC|npc=Martin Holt|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=Ah, so you're the adventurer who's been cooking up a storm around here. Well you'll be pleased to know your hard work was all for nothing. Councillor Hughes has escaped. Lucky her.}} Lydia was tasked to investigate leads on where she might have gone and receives the help of the adventurer who helped arrested her.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commander Fullore|quote=Alright, you can help. But for the duration of this investigation, you're working for me. What I say goes, [...] Right now we don't have any leads on where Councillor Hughes might have gone. I'm heading over to her home to see if there's anything there that can help us.}} With the adventurer's assistance, Sophia is discovered to have planned an escape via [[Veos]]' ship in [[Port Piscarilius]], and Lydia moved quickly to intercept her. However, in a last ditch attempt, Sophia summoned the [[Judge of Yama]], who incinerates her for taking advantage of Yama's generosity and his trust,{{CiteNPC|npc=Judge of Yama|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=You have betrayed the trust of Yama, Sophia Hughes. You have used his generosity to your own advantage. For this, your life is forfeit.}} and proceeds to battle the adventurer, leaving Lydia to deal with [[Councillor Andrews]]' vitriol towards her for her failures in recapturing Sophia.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commander Fullore|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=Councillor Andrews may have been all nice to you, but he's furious with me. He's blamed me for what happened in Port Piscarilius.}}

===Uncovering the Council's corruption===
Before her death, Sophia had mentioned that she and the rest of the Council had done something to a man and his girl,{{CiteNPC|npc=Sophia Hughes|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=You'd think they'd have some loyalty after all we did! After what we did to him. After what we did to his girl! We were in it together until it no longer suited them!}} believed to be [[King Kharedst IV]] and [[Rose]]. Afraid that Andrews would have a close tab on her, she reluctantly asked the adventurer to seek Martin regarding Rose's fate.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commander Fullore|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=Martin. He's leader of Kourend's Royal Society. He knows more about the last royal family than anyone. If anyone can help you find Rose, it's him.}}

Eventually, the adventurer's investigation led them to a small shack at the base of [[Mount Karuulm]] in the [[Kebos Lowlands]], where the uncovering of a hidden entrance to a basement resulted in the discovery of Rose and Councillor [[Liam Orson]], who had been caring for her out of guilt since she entered into a coma. Having been discovered, he confessed to the adventurer and Lydia that the Council had conspired to kill [[King Kharedst IV]], but that it did so out of necessity.{{CiteNPC|npc=Councillor Orson|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=There was an Arceuus mage. He was an expert in curses, and he realised what was happening. He gave us the poison for the King. [...] By then, it was already too late. The King had deteriorated too much. There was only one solution.}} Liam also revealed that the Council remain in contact with the mage who helped them kill the King to obtain potions believed to help treat Rose's condition. The mage was later discovered to be [[Xamphur]], [[Xeric]]'s closest comrade, who had intentionally put Rose into a permanent coma. Lydia was furious at the Council's deception and realized that they had fooled everyone in Kourend.

[[File:A Kingdom Divided - Rose's funeral.png|thumb|260px|The adventurer and Lydia bury Rose, the last princess of Great Kourend.]]
After moving Liam to [[Xeric's Lookout]], while the adventurer was investigating the mage Xamphur, Lydia studied the potions and found that Liam had been telling the truth. However, as there was no hope of waking Rose, she chose to end her suffering and held an impromptu funeral outside the shack.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commander Fullore|loc=A Kingdom Divided|quote=The poison they gave her irreversibly destroyed her mind. There is no cure. Someone else could make the potions, but all they do is prolong her suffering. This is no life for anyone. The truth is, Rose died long ago. All that's left now is an empty shell.}} With Liam's confession and the knowledge of Xamphur's involvement with the Kourend Council, Lydia asked the adventurer to gather the leaders of the five houses, [[Trobin Arceuus]], [[Kandur Hosidius]], [[Vulcana Lovakengj]], [[Shauna Piscarilius]], and [[Shiro Shayzien]], to meet at [[Xeric's Lookout]], where they would decide on the next course of action.

After agreeing on a plan, the leaders of the five houses proceeded to [[Kourend Castle]] and removed the Kourend Council from power.{{CiteNPC|npc=Lord Kandur Hosidius|quote=We, the leaders of the five houses of Great Kourend, declare that the Kourend Council is no longer fit to rule. As such, you are relieved of your positions with immediate effect.}} After disbanding the Council, Lydia attended [[Kandur Hosidius]]' coronation ceremony, only for him to be assassinated almost immediately after. Shortly, [[Artur Hosidius]], Kandur's son, succeeded his father. Lydia continues to investigate the assassination and promises to inform the adventurer of new developments as they come.

